data.title: Lives Up To Its Name
data.text:
Tucked away in downtown Kent's Titusville Station is Perk Up Place Deli.  They have wonderful staff and the food and presentation are very good.  Service is upbeat and quick and the prices are very reasonable.
  The menu has a number of really great choices and they very the menu with specials daily.  Open for Breakfast and Lunch Monday through Friday.  A nice relaxed place to casually dine. George and Lynda

data.title: Great Food
data.text: The Perk Up Place is a small Breakfast and lunch restaurant tucked inside Titusville Station on Gowe Street. It is a great place for made to order deli sandwiches, soups and salads. The fruit cup I had today was fresh and had in it the best grapes I have had all year. They have a daily special also. This restaurant is only open Monday- Friday. They deliver to the local,downtown Kent area. The Perk Up Place is worth a try. I think you will like it.

data.title: Great lunch spot!
data.text: This tucked away place is a great lunch spot. homemade soups, salads and sandwiches and a few yummy desserts. My favorite is Taco salad (currently on Tuesdays)

data.title: A Hidden Gem
data.text: The Perk up Place is open again after a brief time off. This is a hidden Gem in the Tittisville Station Building on Gowe between 1st and 2nd. They serve Breakfast and Lunch Monday - Friday. The food is made to order and is very good. You can call in a order and they will have it ready for you to pick up.
